OL,4,CPROGRAMMES
OL,5,
OL,6,CG1978FThe original run of The Good
OL,7,FLife came to an end shortly after the
OL,8,Fend of the fourth series, with a
OL,9,Fspecial episode titled When I'm
OL,10,FSixty-Five, which was a Royal Command
OL,11,FPerformance in front of The Queen, The
OL,12,FDuke of Edinburgh and senior BBC
OL,13,Fmanagement in TC6.
OL,14,
OL,15,FThe cast and crew were presented to The
OL,16,FQueen and Prince Philip after the
OL,17,Frecording. The episode was originally
OL,18,Fbroadcast in a 45-minute slot (7.40pm -
OL,19,F8.25pm) with footage either side of the
OL,20,F30-minute episode showing the Royal
OL,21,FParty entering and exiting, with
OL,22,Fcommentary by Brian Johnston.
OL,23,Sppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
